examples.en: He banged a teapot on the table.
John banged up his knee playing cricket.
I banged on the door until she let me in.
She banged her funny bone on the doorpost.
Dan banged on her door and rattled the handle.
They wear their hair banged low over their foreheads.
She banged her fist on the table.
He banged up his car in the race.
The old man banged around the house.
Children banged on the desks and shouted.
I fell and banged my head on the pavement.
I banged into an old friend in town today.
This car looks as if it's been banged about.
I've banged into the doorpost and hurt my arm.
The car banged against the garage door and damaged it.
Jess came flying round the corner and banged straight into me.
The landlord wanted to evict the tenants so he banged on the pipes every morning at 3 a.m.
